properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 3:16AM CST until January 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTRY MIX OF FREEZING DRIZZLE AND SNOW EXPECTED TODAY...

.Low pressure approaching from the Northern Plains will produce a
mixture of snow, freezing drizzle and drizzle across northern and
central Wisconsin from mid morning through early this evening.
While snow and ice accumulations are expected to be relatively
light, driving conditions will likely become hazardous in some
areas.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to one inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Southern Marinette County County.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 9 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions by midday. The
hazardous conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
